    <title>droneOS</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><bold>droneOS</bold> is a proprietary, ROS 2-based modular SDK for commanding PX4-compatible autonomous drone fleets. It provides reusable mission logic, low-level PX4 communication, and real-time control infrastructure for scalable, multi-agent operations.</para>
<sect1 id="md_src_drone_core_README_1autotoc_md1">
<title>‚úàÔ∏è Features</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Fleet-level drone management via <computeroutput><ref refid="classDroneAgent" kindref="compound">DroneAgent</ref></computeroutput> and <computeroutput><ref refid="classDroneManager" kindref="compound">DroneManager</ref></computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>YAML-driven waypoint missions with auto-progress logic</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Real-time position tracking using PX4 telemetry</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Modular architecture designed for expansion into AI-driven command layers</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Compatible with PX4 Autopilot and ROS 2 middleware</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Thread-safe drone state management</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Configurable mission parameters and behaviors</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md_src_drone_core_README_1autotoc_md2">
<title>üèóÔ∏è Architecture</title>
<para>The SDK is built around a core set of components:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput><ref refid="classDroneAgent" kindref="compound">DroneAgent</ref></computeroutput>: Individual drone control and state management</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput><ref refid="classDroneManager" kindref="compound">DroneManager</ref></computeroutput>: Fleet-level coordination and mission execution</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Mission Parser: YAML-based mission configuration</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>PX4 Interface: Low-level communication with PX4 autopilot</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md_src_drone_core_README_1autotoc_md3">
<title>üöÄ Getting Started</title>
<para><heading level="2">Requirements</heading>
</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>ROS 2 Humble or newer</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>PX4 Autopilot + <computeroutput>px4_msgs</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>yaml-cpp</computeroutput> and standard ROS 2 build tools</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>C++17 compatible compiler</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Dependencies</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".bash"><codeline><highlight class="normal">#<sp/>Install<sp/>ROS<sp/>2<sp/>dependencies</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">sudo<sp/>apt<sp/>install<sp/>ros-${ROS_DISTRO}-px4-msgs</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">sudo<sp/>apt<sp/>install<sp/>libyaml-cpp-dev</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><heading level="2">Build</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".bash"><codeline><highlight class="normal">cd<sp/>~/ws_droneOS</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">colcon<sp/>build<sp/>--packages-select<sp/>drone_os</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">source<sp/>install/setup.bash</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><heading level="2">Usage</heading>
</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Launch the drone core: <programlisting filename=".bash"><codeline><highlight class="normal">ros2<sp/>launch<sp/>drone_os<sp/>drone_core.launch.py</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Configure missions using YAML files (see examples in <computeroutput>config/</computeroutput>)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Use the ROS 2 API to:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Monitor drone states</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Send commands</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Manage missions</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Coordinate fleet operations</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
